value.0: Hello again. Any luck in locating the Star Sapphire?
Well done, my good <man/woman>. And, as promised, here is your reward.
Hello again. Thank you once again for retrieving the Star Sapphire. Unless you have an unusual taste in rare gems, I am not sure that my wares will interest you much, though.
Greetings, friend! Husher Clay at your service. Actually, I have a proposition for a capable <man/woman> like you.
I'm a collector of rare gems. Right now there's one particular gem I'm interested in: the Star Sapphire.

The Star Sapphire is valuable, that I'll warrant you; but you'll never get more than 600 gold from any other dealer. But it's interesting to me as a collector, so I'm offering substantially more than that.
The Star Sapphire would make a nice addition to my collection. Bring it to me and I'll pay you far more than the sapphire is worth to a more typical buyer.
Excellent. Nobody knows for certain where Layenne was buried, but it's rumored to be somewhere in the mesa to the northeast.
